author: Anonymous Beaker
title: One autograder test failed for PS6
question: In problems 2 and 3 of PS6, my autograded results say that I have one additional test failing. However, test validity, test thoroughness, and submitted tests are all perfectly correct, along with the rest of the additional tests. I assume by this that I understood the problem and executed the solution correctly, so I'm not sure what else I should do?
student_answer:
It sounds your solution is largely, but not completely, correct.  If you carefully create more check-expects, they should reveal the edge case(s) that aren't handled correctly.
It may help to read over the instructions from the very beginning and make sure you haven't missed anything.
